dc_title_s: Monona County, Iowa, 1949, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet labels. Images are photoreductions of mosaics created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol DE. Form of individual image numbering: DE-1F-[number], DE-2F-[number], DE-3F-[number], or DE-4F-[number]. "Flying completed 9-1-49." Flown by Woltz Studios, Des Moines, Iowa. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
dc_publisher_s: United States. Department of Agriculture. Production and Marketing Administration
